 | 

For anyone trying to build with expo locally (without EAS!) with this command:

`npx expo run:android --device`

Ignore "eas credentials" or any instructions telling you to go in your home folder. When you run the build command, Expo will create an /android folder in the folder of the app. In /android/app, there is a debug.keystore file that is auto-generated. This file is the one to be used to generate the SHA-1 fingerprint for local builds with this command (when ran from apps/native):

`keytool -list -v -keystore android/app/debug.keystore -alias androiddebugkey -storepass android -keypass android`

This will generate the correct fingeprint.

